    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Do we want to:\r\n\r\n1. be able to provide manual values to a widget like menu?\r\nexample:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmenu({\r\n  items: [{label: 'Oranges', value: 'orange'}]\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill then be the only values being displayed, and the counts would be also filled by reading the API.\r\n\r\n2. add an option to express \"even if count for this a facet value is 0, I want to keep it\"\r\n\r\nAre those two options in the scope/context of what you proposed?\r\n\r\nAbout 1. We had the requirement/feature idea by @Shipow at some point to be able to just create a menu with predefined items where the order would just stick to this. But if we have other ways of answering 1. (for example, with transformItems in react-instantsearch), then we are fine I guess :)",
